312
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:16,720
Beichuan.

313
00:25:18,550 --> 00:25:19,310
I'm here.

314
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:24,320
If you're thirsty,
pour yourself some water.

315
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,870
Why are you living here?

316
00:25:33,270 --> 00:25:36,160
I'm seeking inspiration among mortals.

317
00:25:36,830 --> 00:25:38,360
What are you talking about?

318
00:25:38,550 --> 00:25:40,240
Mortals?

319
00:25:40,830 --> 00:25:42,030
Are there immortals?

320
00:25:42,670 --> 00:25:44,200
You're classifying people

321
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:45,900
into different ranks.

322
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:48,280
I need to criticize you for that.

323
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:49,480
You have a point.

324
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:51,800
There's quiet within the noise,

325
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:53,610
and noise within the quiet—

326
00:25:53,910 --> 00:25:55,200
it's good for your writing.

327
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:55,880
But

328
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:57,040
living here

329
00:25:57,060 --> 00:25:58,590
means no girls will come by.

330
00:25:59,350 --> 00:26:00,590
If you ever get a girlfriend,

331
00:26:00,590 --> 00:26:02,450
how could you live here like this?

332
00:26:06,070 --> 00:26:07,830
Who says a man

333
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:09,560
must have a woman by his side?

334
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:12,030
And who says a woman

335
00:26:12,170 --> 00:26:13,300
must have a man?

336
00:26:18,550 --> 00:26:22,030
You're not going to say
you like me next, are you?

337
00:26:22,750 --> 00:26:23,360
Get lost.

338
00:26:33,740 --> 00:26:35,260
I saw Ye Xining today.

339
00:26:37,060 --> 00:26:37,740
She's back.

340
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:42,180
How did she react when she saw you?

341
00:26:48,930 --> 00:26:51,570
She ran over to me from far away

342
00:26:53,750 --> 00:26:54,790
and gave me a hug.

343
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:56,350
That's great!

344
00:26:56,510 --> 00:26:58,110
It means she still loves you.

345
00:26:59,750 --> 00:27:00,550
I don't know.

346
00:27:02,580 --> 00:27:04,140
I still don't understand

347
00:27:05,310 --> 00:27:06,710
why she was so determined

348
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:09,350
to break up with me a year ago.

349
00:27:10,070 --> 00:27:12,030
You're driving me crazy
with this attitude.

350
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:13,230
Do you still love her?

351
00:27:16,780 --> 00:27:18,060
Of course not.

352
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:21,680
Bro,

353
00:27:22,270 --> 00:27:23,670
you're quite something.

354
00:27:25,790 --> 00:27:27,790
I've been hesitant to tell you this,

355
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,440
but from the very beginning,

356
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,840
I felt you two
weren't right for each other.

357
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,020
Why?

358
00:27:34,350 --> 00:27:35,040
Why?

359
00:27:40,050 --> 00:27:42,210
It's a feeling I can't explain.

360
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,980
You two need to figure it out yourselves.

361
00:27:53,820 --> 00:27:54,860
I have a cousin

362
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:57,140
who teaches at a university.

363
00:27:57,140 --> 00:27:58,730
I think you should meet her.

364
00:27:59,750 --> 00:28:00,510
Really.

365
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:02,640
I think she's someone

366
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:05,240
who could live with you
in a partition room.

367
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:06,110
Just think—

368
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:07,590
in summer,

369
00:28:07,830 --> 00:28:09,510
you ride your little bike with her

370
00:28:09,510 --> 00:28:11,350
to go grocery shopping

371
00:28:11,430 --> 00:28:12,400
or watch a movie.

372
00:28:12,710 --> 00:28:14,710
She'd feel so happy.

373
00:28:15,170 --> 00:28:16,900
She's not that materialistic.

374
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:30,540
Do you think

375
00:28:32,150 --> 00:28:33,880
the differences between women

376
00:28:34,570 --> 00:28:35,920
can be that big?

377
00:28:36,030 --> 00:28:36,880
Of course.

378
00:28:39,350 --> 00:28:40,680
What about between men?

379
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:46,040
It's the same.

380
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:56,920
I don't think so.

381
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:03,270
Xiang Beichuan...

382
00:29:09,830 --> 00:29:12,000
This little house is just a storage now.

383
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:12,750
Nobody lives here.

384
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:15,310
I made some money and moved out.

385
00:29:16,030 --> 00:29:17,240
You're going to live here
now that you're back?

386
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:17,830
Yes.

387
00:29:17,830 --> 00:29:18,530
You'll live here?

388
00:29:18,530 --> 00:29:19,330
Alright then.

389
00:29:19,790 --> 00:29:21,720
I'll clean it up for you tomorrow.

390
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:22,830
Then you can move in.

391
00:29:22,830 --> 00:29:23,450
Okay.

392
00:29:25,250 --> 00:29:27,160
Now that you're back from Europe,

393
00:29:27,830 --> 00:29:29,310
